T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1368
EP  - 1379
VL  - 28
IS  - 12
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The calculation of margin for investor's option accounts is a complex and costly problem for brokerage houses. The existing procedures usually involve a heuristic requiring sequential computations. These are shown to be inefficient and suboptimal. A simple transportation formulation is presented which permits a direct computation of minimum margin and shows considerable savings when compared with existing heuristic procedures.
AB  - The calculation of margin for investor's option accounts is a complex and costly problem for brokerage houses. The existing procedures usually involve a heuristic requiring sequential computations. These are shown to be inefficient and suboptimal. A simple transportation formulation is presented which permits a direct computation of minimum margin and shows considerable savings when compared with existing heuristic procedures.
